115UVW_INLINE Passwd Utilities::OS::passwd() noexcept {
116 auto deleter = [](uv_passwd_t *passwd){
117 uv_os_free_passwd(passwd);
118 delete passwd;
119 };
120
121 std::shared_ptr<uv_passwd_t> ptr{new uv_passwd_t, std::move(deleter)};
122 uv_os_get_passwd(ptr.get());
123 return ptr;
124}

127UVW_INLINE int Utilities::osPriority(PidType pid) {
128 int prio = 0;
129
130 if(uv_os_getpriority(pid, &prio)) {
131 prio = UV_PRIORITY_LOW + 1;
132 }
133
134 return prio;
135}

143UVW_INLINE HandleType Utilities::guessHandle(HandleCategory category) noexcept {
144 switch(category) {
145 case UV_ASYNC:
146 return HandleType::ASYNC;
147 case UV_CHECK:
148 return HandleType::CHECK;
149 case UV_FS_EVENT:
150 return HandleType::FS_EVENT;
151 case UV_FS_POLL:
152 return HandleType::FS_POLL;
153 case UV_HANDLE:
154 return HandleType::HANDLE;
155 case UV_IDLE:
156 return HandleType::IDLE;
157 case UV_NAMED_PIPE:
158 return HandleType::PIPE;
159 case UV_POLL:
160 return HandleType::POLL;
161 case UV_PREPARE:
162 return HandleType::PREPARE;
163 case UV_PROCESS:
164 return HandleType::PROCESS;
165 case UV_STREAM:
166 return HandleType::STREAM;
167 case UV_TCP:
168 return HandleType::TCP;
169 case UV_TIMER:
170 return HandleType::TIMER;
171 case UV_TTY:
172 return HandleType::TTY;
173 case UV_UDP:
174 return HandleType::UDP;
175 case UV_SIGNAL:
176 return HandleType::SIGNAL;
177 case UV_FILE:
178 return HandleType::FILE;
179 default:
180 return HandleType::UNKNOWN;
181 }
182}
183

185UVW_INLINE HandleType Utilities::guessHandle(FileHandle file) noexcept {
186 HandleCategory category = uv_guess_handle(file);
187 return guessHandle(category);
188}

191UVW_INLINE std::vector<CPUInfo> Utilities::cpuInfo() noexcept {
192 std::vector<CPUInfo> cpuinfos;
193
194 uv_cpu_info_t *infos;
195 int count;
196
197 if(0 == uv_cpu_info(&infos, &count)) {
198 std::for_each(infos, infos+count, [&cpuinfos](const auto &info) {
199 cpuinfos.push_back({ info.model, info.speed, info.cpu_times });
200 });
201
202 uv_free_cpu_info(infos, count);
203 }
204
205 return cpuinfos;
206}

209UVW_INLINE std::vector<InterfaceAddress> Utilities::interfaceAddresses() noexcept {
210 std::vector<InterfaceAddress> interfaces;
211
212 uv_interface_address_t *ifaces{nullptr};
213 int count{0};
214
215 if(0 == uv_interface_addresses(&ifaces, &count)) {
216 std::for_each(ifaces, ifaces+count, [&interfaces](const auto &iface) {
217 InterfaceAddress interfaceAddress;
218
219 interfaceAddress.name = iface.name;
220 std::copy(iface.phys_addr, (iface.phys_addr+6), interfaceAddress.physical);
221 interfaceAddress.internal = iface.is_internal == 0 ? false : true;
222
223 if(iface.address.address4.sin_family == AF_INET) {
224 interfaceAddress.address = details::address<IPv4>(&iface.address.address4);
225 interfaceAddress.netmask = details::address<IPv4>(&iface.netmask.netmask4);
226 } else if(iface.address.address4.sin_family == AF_INET6) {
227 interfaceAddress.address = details::address<IPv6>(&iface.address.address6);
228 interfaceAddress.netmask = details::address<IPv6>(&iface.netmask.netmask6);
229 }
230
231 interfaces.push_back(std::move(interfaceAddress));
232 });
233
234 uv_free_interface_addresses(ifaces, count);
235 }
236
237 return interfaces;
238}

268UVW_INLINE std::string Utilities::processTitle() {
269 std::size_t size = details::DEFAULT_SIZE;
270 char buf[details::DEFAULT_SIZE];
271 std::string str{};
272
273 if(0 == uv_get_process_title(buf, size)) {
274 str.assign(buf, size);
275 }
276
277 return str;
278}
